Press Releases.Title: No New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
1. As of 17 December 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed that there are no new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection.

2. There are 24 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice or isolated upon arrival in Singapore. Amongst them, 13 are returning Singaporeans or Singapore Permanent Residents.

3. We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.
